parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Bendix ABS system can cause the brakes to lock up while driving, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The brakes lock up without warning
the brake pedal becomes hard
the ABS braking light appears on the dashboard
and the vehicle may experience sudden loss of braking ability.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake hydraulic system can cause the brake pedal to become hard or soft, leading to reduced braking ability, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels hard or spongy
the brake pedal travels to the floor
the brakes make noise or vibrate
and the vehicle may experience sudden loss of braking ability.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Component Failure (Drums, Shoes, Wheel Cylinders, Cables)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of brake components can cause reduced braking ability, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The brakes make noise or vibrate
the brake pedal feels hard or spongy
the brake pedal travels to the floor
and the vehicle may experience sudden loss of braking ability.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected lockup of the right rear wheel can cause the vehicle to skid, losing traction and control, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The right rear wheel locks up
the vehicle skids or loses traction
the vehicle pulls to one side
the driver experiences a loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the driver's seat brackets can cause the seat to collapse or break, leading to a loss of control while driving, which can increase the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The driver's seat collapses or breaks while driving
the seat brackets fall off
the seat becomes unstable or wobbly
the driver experiences difficulty maintaining control of the vehicle.
